pull_request.title: [WIP] Architecture: Separate marketing site from authenticated application
pull_request.body:
Thanks for assigning this issue to me. I'm starting to work on it and will keep this PR's description up to date as I form a plan and make progress.

Original issue description:

> ## Problem
> Currently, the homepage (`/app/src/app/page.tsx`) serves as both marketing landing page AND authenticated dashboard. This creates poor UX where authenticated users see marketing content instead of their dashboard.
> 
> ## Current Issues
> - No authentication-based routing separation
> - Marketing content mixed with app functionality  
> - Confusing user experience for authenticated users
> - No clear entry point differentiation
> - SEO issues with mixed content purpose
> 
> ## Proposed Solution
> 
> ### 1. Create Separate Route Structure
> ```
> Marketing Site:
> â”œâ”€â”€ / (homepage - unauthenticated)
> â”œâ”€â”€ /about  
> â”œâ”€â”€ /pricing
> â”œâ”€â”€ /contact
> â”œâ”€â”€ /auth/login
> â”œâ”€â”€ /auth/signup
> â””â”€â”€ /auth/forgot-password
> 
> Authenticated App:
> â”œâ”€â”€ /dashboard (main authenticated entry)
> â”œâ”€â”€ /clubs/[id]
> â”œâ”€â”€ /meetings/[id] 
> â”œâ”€â”€ /profile
> â”œâ”€â”€ /settings
> â””â”€â”€ /learning/[course]
> ```
> 
> ### 2. Implement Route Protection
> **Create Middleware**: `/app/src/middleware.ts`
> ```typescript
> export function middleware(request: NextRequest) {
>   const { pathname } = request.nextUrl;
>   const token = request.cookies.get('auth_token');
>   
>   // Redirect authenticated users from marketing to dashboard
>   if (token && isMarketingPage(pathname)) {
>     return NextResponse.redirect('/dashboard');
>   }
>   
>   // Redirect unauthenticated users from app to login
>   if (\!token && isAppPage(pathname)) {
>     return NextResponse.redirect('/auth/login');
>   }
> }
> ```
> 
> ### 3. Create Dedicated Layouts
> **Marketing Layout**: `app/(marketing)/layout.tsx`
> - Marketing-focused navigation
> - Call-to-action buttons
> - SEO optimizations
> - No authenticated user state
> 
> **App Layout**: `app/(app)/layout.tsx` 
> - Application navigation
> - User profile dropdown
> - Notification center
> - Club/meeting context
> 
> ### 4. Update Components
> **Navigation Component Separation**:
> - `MarketingNavigation.tsx` - For unauthenticated users
> - `AppNavigation.tsx` - For authenticated users  
> - Context-aware component switching
> 
> ## Technical Requirements
> - [ ] Create `/dashboard` route as main authenticated entry point
> - [ ] Move current homepage features to `/dashboard`
> - [ ] Design new marketing homepage at `/`
> - [ ] Add route protection middleware
> - [ ] Implement authentication-based redirects
> - [ ] Create separate layout components
> - [ ] Update navigation components for context switching
> - [ ] Add loading states for auth checks
> - [ ] Implement proper error boundaries
> 
> ## Files to Create/Modify
> ```
> New Files:
> â”œâ”€â”€ app/(marketing)/
> â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ layout.tsx
> â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ page.tsx (new marketing homepage)
> â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ about/page.tsx
> â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ pricing/page.tsx
> â”‚   â””â”€â”€ contact/page.tsx
> â”œâ”€â”€ app/(app)/
> â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ layout.tsx
> â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ dashboard/page.tsx (moved from current homepage)
> â”‚   â””â”€â”€ [existing app routes]
> â”œâ”€â”€ src/components/MarketingNavigation.tsx
> â”œâ”€â”€ src/components/AppNavigation.tsx
> â””â”€â”€ middleware.ts
> 
> Modified Files:
> â”œâ”€â”€ app/page.tsx (convert to marketing homepage)
> â”œâ”€â”€ src/components/Navigation.tsx (add context awareness)
> â”œâ”€â”€ src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx (handle routing logic)
> â””â”€â”€ app/layout.tsx (conditional layouts)
> ```
> 
> ## SEO Considerations
> - Separate meta tags for marketing vs app pages
> - Marketing pages optimized for search engines
> - App pages excluded from search indexing
> - Proper canonical URLs for marketing content
> 
> ## User Experience Flow
> 1. **Unauthenticated User**: Lands on marketing site â†’ Signs up â†’ Redirected to dashboard
> 2. **Authenticated User**: Direct access to `/` â†’ Auto-redirected to `/dashboard`  
> 3. **Logout**: Redirect from app pages to marketing homepage
> 
> ## Priority
> **P0 - Critical for Production UX**
> 
> Labels: `architecture`, `authentication`, `routing`, `UX`, `P0`

issue.body:
**Bug Description**
Subject: SSH Authentication Failure After macOS Keychain Integration - Critical Issue for Pro Plan Users

Description:
I am experiencing a critical authentication issue with Claude Code that has severely impacted my workflow. This problem started approximately 2-3 days ago and appears to be related to the recent change that moved API key storage to macOS Keychain.

Issue Details:
- For the past month, Claude Code worked perfectly via SSH connections
- Since ~2-3 days ago, SSH authentication completely fails with "Missing API key Â· Run /login" 
- Physical machine access still works normally
- I am a Claude.ai Pro Plan subscriber (not API account user)
- The issue occurs specifically when accessing Claude Code through SSH clients like Terminus

Timeline:
- Previous month: SSH access worked flawlessly
- Recent days: Complete SSH authentication failure
- Physical machine: Still functional

Technical Analysis:
Based on the changelog, Claude Code now stores "(Mac-only) API keys in macOS Keychain". This change appears to have broken SSH access because:
1. SSH sessions cannot access the macOS Keychain that requires GUI session context
2. OAuth authentication completes successfully in browser but tokens are not accessible to SSH sessions
3. Physical machine works because it has full GUI session access to Keychain

Steps to Reproduce:
1. SSH into macOS host with Claude Code installed
2. Run `claude` command
3. Execute `/login`
4. Complete OAuth authentication in browser (shows "Login successful")
5. Claude Code still displays "Missing API key Â· Run /login"
6. `/status` shows "Auth Token: [REDACTED] despite successful login

Impact:
This is a critical regression that has completely broken my development workflow. As a Pro Plan subscriber, I cannot use the environment variables workaround since that requires API account access. I believe many SSH users are experiencing this same issue.

- Claude Code version: [current version]
- Installation: npm global

- Access method: SSH (Terminus, etc.)

This issue severely impacts user experience and appears to affect many SSH users. Please:
1. Provide immediate acknowledgment of this regression
2. Prioritize a fix for SSH authentication with macOS Keychain
3. Consider reverting the Keychain-only approach or providing SSH-compatible alternatives
4. Send email updates on progress and resolution

I rely heavily on Claude Code for my development work and this regression has made the tool completely unusable in my primary workflow. Please treat this as a high-priority issue and provide email feedback on the resolution timeline.
